# Static sites still deserve a real framework

Static output does not mean primitive tooling. A useful framework should still
provide layouts, components, route conventions, content collections, diagnostics,
and a repeatable deployment artifact.

Axonyx keeps those concerns together while leaving the browser with clean HTML
and only the behavior a component actually needs.
